  "text": "It has been demonstrated that in most PCa patients, the usual sites of metastases are the pelvic LNs and/or the hematopoietic red marrow of the axial skeleton [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Visceral metastases are rare and usually appear in later stages of the disease [CITATION_4] .",
